properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 27 at 9:41AM AKST until January 27 at 7:00PM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow and blowing snow expected. Total snow accumulations
of 4 to 8 inches, with locally higher amounts near Whittier.
Winds gusting 35 to 50 mph at times in Seward and Whittier.

* WHERE...Whittier, Seward, and along the Seward Highway. Expect
the worst conditions from Moose Pass through Seward and near
Whittier.

* WHEN...Until 7 PM AKST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Areas of blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The combination of snow and blowing snow
may reduce visibility as low as one quarter of a mile at times
due to gusty westerly winds in Whittier and northerly winds in
Seward. Wind gusts will also occasionally reduce visibility
along the Seward Highway, especially through Turnagain Pass. Any
accumulating snow will be powdery and easily resuspended by
fast moving vehicles, substantially reduce visibilities.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit
511.alaska.gov.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM AKST THIS EVENING
